This is a missed-optimization in InstCombine.

The following program reveals the missed optimization.
The source program is
```llvm
define <8 x i1> @fcmp_one_sel_x_negx_vec(<8 x float> %x) {
  %f = fcmp one <8 x float> %x, zeroinitializer
  %neg = fneg <8 x float> %x
  %sel = select <8 x i1> %f, <8 x float> %x, <8 x float> %neg
  %res = fcmp one <8 x float> %sel, zeroinitializer
  ret <8 x i1> %res
}

```

However, current LLVM cannot optimize the source program. The expected optimized program is
```llvm
define <8 x i1> @fcmp_one_sel_x_negx_vec(<8 x float> %x) {
  %res = fcmp one <8 x float> %x, zeroinitializer
  ret <8 x i1> %res
}

```
